SIMPLE: twenty-fourmo
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Twenty-fourmo
<hw>Twen`ty-four"mo</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having
twenty-four leaves to a sheet; <as>as, a <ex>twenty-fourmo</ex> form,
book, leaf, size, etc</as>.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>A book
composed of sheets, each of which is folded into twenty-four leaves;
hence, indicating more or less definitely a size of book whose sheets
are so folded; -- usually written 24mo, or 24⟦deg⟧.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>twenty-four-seven</ent>⟦br⟧
